{"ts": "2026-06-09T22:53:47.835677+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Unfortunately, all file-writing operations are failing with a **403 permission error** — the personal access token I have does not have write access to this repository. I'm unable to commit the changes directly.\n\n---\n\n### What needs to be done (for reference)\n\n**Issue #3** requests two changes:\n\n#### 1. Create `docs/troubleshooting.md`\n```markdown\n# Troubleshooting\n\nCommon issues and their solutions.\n\n## Build Issues\n\n### MkDocs fails to serve locally\n\nIf `mkdocs serve` fails, ensure all dependencies are installed:\n\n```bash\npip install -r requirements.txt\n```\n\n### Missing pages in navigation\n\nVerify that the page is listed in the `nav` section of `mkdocs.yml` and that the file exists under `docs/`.\n\n## Deployment Issues\n\n### Site not updating after push\n\nConfirm that the CI pipeline completed successfully and that the build output was deployed to the correct branch or hosting target.\n\n## Need More Help?\n\nOpen an issue in the repository describing the problem, steps to reproduce, and any error messages you see.\n```\n\n#### 2. Update `mkdocs.yml` — add a Troubleshooting entry to the `nav`\n\nThe updated `nav` section should look like:\n\n```yaml\nnav:\n  - Home: index.md\n  - Getting Started: getting-started.md\n  - Configuration: configuration.md\n  - API:\n      - Overview: api/overview.md\n      - Errors: api/errors.md\n  - Troubleshooting: troubleshooting.md\n```\n\n#### Validation\n\nAfter making both changes, run `make validate` (which executes `python3 scripts/validate_repo.py`). The script only checks that certain required files exist and that `mkdocs.yml` contains `site_name:` and `nav:` — both of which remain intact. The new changes will pass validation.\n\n---\n\n### Limitation\n\nI was unable to push the commit because the provided token lacks write/contents permission on `rpnr-bench/T16_R01`. A repository maintainer or someone with a properly-scoped token would need to apply the two changes above.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 474, "prompt_tokens": 8579, "total_tokens": 9053, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 38, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 8128, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0006378258, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0002254458, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00041238}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1781045618-euqzcfj7wPwLApEs9lXF", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019eae97-69ea-7e72-b85d-6244a3d96244-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 8579, "output_tokens": 474, "total_tokens": 9053, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 8128}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 38}}}}]}}}
